    <div class="field field-name-title field-type-ds field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="dc:title"><h1 class="h4">DrupalCon Portland 2013: Impressions and experiences</h1></div></div></div><div class="meta">By <a href="/category/author/tim-deeson">Tim Deeson</a> | 5th June 2013</div><div class="field field-name-field-image field-type-image field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://deeson-online.co.uk/sites/default/files/styles/580-360/public/post/drupal-portland.jpg" alt="" /></div></div></div><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p class="p1">I returned from <a href="https://portland2013.drupal.org/">DrupalCon Portland</a> recently. As usual it was a tidalwave of new information, new contacts and catching up with longstanding friends and acquaintances.</p>
<h2>Drupal 8 Roadmap</h2>
<p class="p1"><a href="http://buytaert.net/resume">Dries' keynote</a> gave a great overview of progress on Drupal 8 and some of the features that will have direct benefit to project delivery and client.</p>
